    #application_arrownav_page_3.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_3
        .offset25
          %h3 ...practise with someone now
        .set-3a
          %h4 i) Connect
          %p Click the 'Join' button to connect to case roulette
          %p You are now visible as 'online' to all other users on the roulette page
          %p Sit back, relax and wait for other users to contact you
        .set-3b
          %h4 ii) Roulette Request
          %p When another user sends you a request, a popup will appear on your screen, showing the other user's status and their Skype address.
          %p Click the 'call me' button, to call them on Skype and start a case, if you wish
          %p Alternatively find candidates in the list, and send them a request yourself
        .set-3c
          %h4 iii) Jump to Skype to start a case
          %p Candidates on the roulette are likely not to be your case partners, so as a security measure, to send them feedback on the case, ask the interviewee for their 'roulette token', a ranomly generated code, at the top of the page.
          %p Enter their code into your roulette window to be taken to a feedback form for them

    #application_arrownav_page_4.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_4
        .offset15
          %h3 ...fill out a feedback form for your case partner
        .set-4a
          %p This form has been carefully designed by top-3 firm consultants with many years of interviewing experience
        .set-4b
          %h4 ii) Scoring Criteria
          %p The three main criteria
          %ul
            %li Business Analytics
            %li Interperonsal
            %li Structure
          %p ...and their sub-criteria, comprise everything interviewers look for, and on which candidates can fail
          %p
            %b If this is your first time using this form, for the benefit of your case partner, take time to carefully read the descriptions of each sub-criteria, by moving your mouse over each
        .set-4c
          %h4 iii) Move the Sliders
          %p Move the sliders to give your case partner a score between 1-10 for each sub-criteria - you are required to give a score on each.
          %p 1 is the worst, 10 is the best - anything below 5 should be considered a bad score.
          %p The sub-scriteria scores are averaged to give a total score for the main critera
        .set-4d
          %h4 iv) Make Comments
          %p Enter your comments in the text boxes on the right for each criteria
          %p Use the controls to structure your comments with bullet points
          %p Be as detailed, but concise as possible
        .set-4e
          %h4 i) Top 3 Recommendations
          %p Specify three areas they should prioritise going forward

    #application_arrownav_page_5.arrownav_page
